{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Butter sides and base of a deep cake tin (Ø 20 cm) - must not be loose-bottomed!","Set a bowl on mixing bowl lid and place lemon juice and milk in it then set aside to sour.","Place 50 g butter and 110 g sugar in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>3 min\/90°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Pour into prepared tin, spreading it out evenly. Drain pears through simmering basket then arrange pears on butter-sugar topping, cut side down if using halves and place walnuts or pecans between pears.","Place 50 g butter in mixing bowl and heat <nobr>1 min\/50°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add 110 g brown sugar, reserved soured milk, black treacle and egg then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>.","Add plain flour, ground cinnamon, ground ginger, bicarbonate of soda, salt, ground nutmeg and ground cloves then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Pour on top of pears - this is a very liquid cake mixture.","Bake 40-50 minutes (180°C) or until a skewer inserted in middle comes out clean. Leave to cool 15 minutes in the tin then turn out onto a plate and serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g butter, cut in pieces, plus extra for greasing","2 tsp lemon juice","110 g milk","220 g brown sugar","400 g tin of pear halves","30 g walnut halves","75 g black treacle","1 large egg","110 g plain flour","2 tsp ground cinnamon","1 tsp ground ginger","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","¼ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","1 pinch ground cloves"]}],"id":"r80569","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-0swVVl7np_Y\/XZWfJFaq4-I\/AAAAAAAAe_k\/-nQ2b2v0178WoBfKtSsbpo7n8Y0RevDBACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_pOJ7K8bcQADbGeEQ.png","title":"Upside-down Gingerbread with Pears","publishedAt":"2015-05-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.5 g","fat":"9.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"32.8 g","calories":"974 kJ \/ 226 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 20 cm), bowl, skewer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve with cream or vanilla ice c